--------------------------------------------------Binary Classification using PCA----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Developed by: Hari Shrawgi

Language: MATLAB

--------------------------------------------------Binary Classification using PCA----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The scripts together constitute a binary classifier of images using PCA.
The method works by finding the subspace of the principal components of both the classes first using the training data.
Then, we use the projections onto these subspaces to judge the closeness of a test data point to classify the point.

Following are descriptions of the various scripts:

1. read_data.m: The script reads in the image data according to the particular format the data is in. Then it also pre-processes the data.
2. get_topk_U.m: Finds the top k principal components.
3. misclassifications.m: Implementation of the classifier which also counts the number of misclassifications as a measure of performance.

